[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-based buffer overflow was detected by AddressSanitizer in the libexif [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary while running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow occurs when the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `exif_get_sshort` reads one byte past the end of a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte heap [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation. This error is triggered during the processing of Apple maker-note data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min an EXIF parsing routine.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  While fuzzing the EXIF parsing code via the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read beyond the allocated buffer. The faulty read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens in `exif_get_sshort` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min exif-utils.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is used to extract signed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m16[0m[39m-bit values from input data.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Heap-buffer-overflow: an out-of-bounds read of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m past a heap allocation [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Execution trace and key observations  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The fuzzer allocates a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte buffer to hold EXIF data.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_get_sshort` attempts to read two bytes from this buffer at an offset [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat lies five bytes beyond the buffer’s end [0m[1;39m([0m[39maddress [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Call chain:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - exif_get_sshort [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-utils.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-utils.[0m[1;92mc:104[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - exif_mnote_data_apple_load [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapple/exif-mnote-data-apple.[0m[1;92mc:110:29[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - exif_data_load_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:1010[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - exif_data_new_from_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif_from_data_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:51[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • exif-utils.c, specifically the implementation of `exif_get_sshort` and its [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c, around the logic in `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat advances the data pointer and invokes the short-read function  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • exif-data.c, to understand how input buffers are allocated, sized, and passed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdown to low-level getter functions  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, as an entry point, to verify [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer lengths supplied to libexif routines  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis evaluation report documents the overflow in the EXIF parsing path without [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspeculating on root causes or proposing fixes.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Array cookie:            ac[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Intra object redzone:    bb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m14[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp9d4swz0y[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered inside exif_get_sshort when [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing MakerNote data in exif_mnote_data_apple_load. The patch attempt added [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks around reads of the byte‐order marker and the tag/format/components [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields to prevent out-of-bounds access and return early on corrupt data. After [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the fuzzer no longer reports the overflow, but LeakSanitizer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetects [0m[1;36m39[0m[39m small heap‐memory leaks originating from calls to calloc in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_mnote_data_apple_load that are no longer freed on the new early-exit paths.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• A libFuzzer run on exif_from_data_fuzzer with AddressSanitizer enabled crashed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a heap-buffer-overflow.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The overflow occurred in exif_get_sshort [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-utils.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, called by [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_mnote_data_apple_load [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-mnote-data-apple.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Sanitizer log shows a one‐byte read at buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m past a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m‐byte allocation [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mofs based on MakerNote offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The stack trace leads from exif_mnote_data_apple_load through exif_data_load_data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the fuzz target.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• In exif-mnote-data-apple.c, before reading the two‐byte byte‐order marker at [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m..ofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, a check was added: if ofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[39m ≥ buf_size, log corrupt data and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• In the tag/format/components loop, before calling exif_get_short/long on buf+ofs,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuf+ofs+[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, buf+ofs+[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, a check was added: if ofs+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > buf_size, log corrupt data and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• These guards prevent the original overflow by exiting early when the buffer is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoo small.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The fuzzer run no longer reports a buffer‐overflow.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• LeakSanitizer reports [0m[1;36m39[0m[39m [0m[1;35mbyte[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m leaked in [0m[1;36m39[0m[39m allocations, all from calloc in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_mnote_data_apple_load.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The early returns introduced by the patch skip the normal cleanup path, so the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory allocated for the MakerNote data structure and its entries is not freed.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• exif_mnote_data_apple_load: allocation of the mnote data structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalloc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory for entries—verify all error/return paths free these allocations.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• exif_data_load_data and exif_data_free_data: ensure consistent cleanup when any [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloading function returns early.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Other MakerNote loaders in libexif [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., Panasonic, Olympus[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: check for similar [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing frees on error returns.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The overall lifecycle of ExifMnoteData objects: audit for leaks when parsing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maborts due to corrupt data.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue was discovered by running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` against [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif’s Apple MakerNote loader. AddressSanitizer reported a one-byte [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `exif_get_sshort`, called from [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`. A patch was attempted in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd multiple buffer-size checks before reading from `buf` and to call [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_free` on error paths. After applying the patch, the build failed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat link time with “undefined reference to `exif_mnote_data_free`” and a DWARF [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror, preventing a successful compile.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzer run invoked `exif_from_data_fuzzer` on a test input of roughly [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` → `exif_get_short` → `exif_get_sshort` reading [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma byte outside the allocated region.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan summary: heap-buffer-overflow on a read [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No prior bounds checks guarded the reads of the byte-order marker or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent TIFF entries in the MakerNote data.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens before reading the TIFF header within the MakerNote — [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically at offsets `ofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m` and `ofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[39m`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After determining byte order, `tcount` is read from `buf+ofs+[0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverifying that those bytes exist.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside the loop over `tcount`, each entry reads [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte tags/formats and [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent counts without any per-entry bounds checks.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Early returns on corrupt data did not free the partially constructed metadata [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ExifMnoteData`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, the following changes were made:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - At the top of `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`, retain the existing check for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`buf_size < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before reading `buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, add:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m >= buf_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the “unrecognized byte order” branch, replace the bare return with a call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `[0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After reading `tcount`, revalidate:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside the loop over `i < tcount`, before reading each [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte directory entry:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > buf_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Updated the formatting of logging calls for consistency.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During compilation/linking, the error surfaced:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     undefined reference to `exif_mnote_data_free'[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m0x515000000580[0m[39m: [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m[39m [0m[1;36m00[0m                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Intra object redzone:    bb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m14[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp9d4swz0y[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApple MakerNote loader. When parsing a malformed MakerNote segment, the code reads [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpast the end of the allocated buffer in `exif_get_sshort`, leading to a one-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe submitted patch augments `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c` with explicit [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks before each multi-byte read and calls `[0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror paths to free the MakerNote data structure early. These additions prevent the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal out-of-bounds access.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer run no longer reports buffer overflows—but it [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes reveal a use-after-free in `exif_mnote_data_count` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled from the fuzzer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness’s `mnote_dump`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The patch’s early `exif_mnote_data_unref` calls release [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe data structure, yet subsequent code still accesses freed memory.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invokes `exif_from_data_fuzzer`, which in turn calls into [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` and ultimately `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, after computing an offset `ofs = d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code unconditionally does:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs, …[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  without verifying that `ofs + [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m < buf_size`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- With a small input buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallocated [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, these reads can exceed buffer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds. ASan reports a heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_get_sshort` at offset ~[0m[1;36m512[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is one byte but still critical.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash stack traces point at the Apple-specific loader [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the utility function `exif_get_sshort` in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif-utils.c`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No earlier bounds checks guard the indexing around `ofs + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch updates `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c` by:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Macro-level guard for minimal size**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   At the top of `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`, unchanged: check `buf_size < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Byte-order marker check**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Before inspecting `buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` and `buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, add:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m >= buf_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Tag count sanity check**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Before computing `tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, ensure `buf_size >= [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m+tcount*[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, and on [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure free `md`.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Per-entry guards**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Within the loop over `tcount`, test `ofs + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > buf_size` before each group of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_short`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`exif_get_long` reads, freeing `md` on error.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Cleanup on all early returns**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Each error path now calls `[0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before returning.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis patch successfully prevents the original buffer overflow: no reads go past [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`buf_size - [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result & New Finding[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding and re-running the fuzzer, ASan no longer flags a buffer overflow.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, a new error appears:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-use-after-free in exif_mnote_data_count[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mREAD of size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m… thread T0[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m exif_mnote_data_count in exif-mnote-data.[0m[1;92mc:112:24[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m mnote_dump in exif_from_data_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:24:19[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    …[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFreed by thread T0 here:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m exif_mnote_data_free in exif-mnote-data.[0m[1;92mc:66:2[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m exif_mnote_data_unref in exif-mnote-data.[0m[1;92mc:76:3[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m exif_data_load_data in exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:1010:2[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m exif_data_new_from_data …[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey points:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch’s early `[0m[1;35mexif_mnote_data_unref[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` frees the MakerNote data [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_free` → `free`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After `exif_data_new_from_data` returns, the fuzzer harness calls `mnote_dump`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich invokes `exif_mnote_data_count` on the already freed structure.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- That leads to a heap-use-after-free reading from the deallocated block.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a complete view of underlying issues, the following code regions warrant [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcloser review:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Error-Path Lifecycle**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How and when `exif_mnote_data_unref` is called versus when higher-level code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpects `md` to remain valid.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether early unref should detach the structure from the parent EXIF data so [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallers don’t access it.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Caller Expectations**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: specifically `mnote_dump` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand subsequent calls that assume `md` is still valid.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The contract of `exif_data_new_from_data`—does it guarantee a valid MakerNote [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meven on parse errors?[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Core EXIF Data Loading**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `interpret_maker_note` in `exif-data.c`, which allocates `md` via [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_new`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The pointer flow from `interpret_maker_note` back to `exif_data_new_from_data`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the ownership semantics of `md`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Apple Loader vs. Generic Logic**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interplay between `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mApple-specific[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_count` [0m[35m/[0m[39m dumping routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgeneric in `exif-mnote-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic fix will require aligning the loader’s error handling with the callers’ [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifecycle assumptions so that `md` isn’t freed while still in use.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-buffer-overflow was uncovered by AddressSanitizer in libexif’s maker-note [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser when running the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The crash occurs in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_sshort` after reading beyond a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte buffer region in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`. A patch was attempted on [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c` to add bounds checks around multiple multibyte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads and data-unpacking loops. When building after the patch, the compiler emitted[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors: calls to `[0m[1;35mexif_mem_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39md->mem, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fail because `struct [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m_ExifMnoteDataApple` has no `mem` member.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer `exif_from_data_fuzzer` invokes `exif_data_new_from_data`, which calls[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto the Apple maker-note loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_get_sshort` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcalled by `exif_get_short`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at an offset past the end of a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace highlights:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_get_sshort [0m[35m/[0m[39m exif_get_short in `exif-utils.c`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_mnote_data_apple_load in `apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data [0m[35m/[0m[39m exif_data_new_from_data in `exif-data.c`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput in the harness[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow address is [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes beyond the allocated buffer, indicating missing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary checks before accessing maker-note fields.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Important Observations[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is triggered by unvalidated reads of multi-byte fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbyte-order [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarkers, tag counts, IFD entries[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the maker-note data.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The region being read spans maker-note offsets [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ofs + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`, `ofs + [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m`, `ofs + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m..[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m`, and further entry data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The heap allocation for the input buffer is exactly [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m bytes, so any access [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond index [0m[1;36m511[0m[39m is out of bounds.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash reproducibly occurs under AddressSanitizer, confirming a deterministic [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- File modified: `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added checks before each critical read:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Maker-note byte-order marker at `buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m..ofs+[0m[1;36m13[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Tag count at `buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mofs+[0m[1;36m14[0m[39m..ofs+[0m[1;36m15[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Total IFD table size validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Per-entry bounds checks for [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte entry header.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Data pointer range check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`dofs + dsize` vs. `buf_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- On any failure, log `EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA`, free `d->entries`, set [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`d->count = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, and return early.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch used `[0m[1;35mexif_mem_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39md->mem, d->entries[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to free entries.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation errors in `apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • “no member named ‘mem’ in ‘struct _ExifMnoteDataApple’” at six call sites of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexif_mem_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39md->mem, d->entries[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- These errors indicate a mismatch between the patch’s use of a `mem` field and the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mactual structure definition.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The build fails before further validation of the bounds-check logic.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Further Investigation[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and fix the overflow, review:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Struct Definitions**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – `_ExifMnoteDataApple` in the header to identify how memory is managed and what[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfree functions are available.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – How `d->entries` is allocated and which allocator/context should be used for [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory Management APIs**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The intended use of `[0m[1;35mexif_mem_free[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` across the codebase and its expected [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marguments.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Alternative free paths in maker-note loaders [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., cleanup in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexif_data_free[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Bounds-Checking Consistency**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Similar IFD parsing code in other maker-note handlers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in other [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer Size Origin**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Code paths in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` beyond the IFD loop that might also [0m   [2m                [0m
